Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // App lost focus (e.g., notification shade pulled down)
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // App fully backgrounded
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // App entered background
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- Android `OnPause` maps to the cross-platform `Deactivated` event (lost focus, may still be visible). `OnStop` maps to `Stopped` (fully backgrounded).
- iOS `DidEnterBackground` maps to `Stopped`.
- Keep handlers fast (<2 seconds) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS.

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need platform-specific APIs, you can use the `Window.Stopped` event instead — it fires on both platforms when the app backgrounds:

```csharp
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* save state here */ };
    return window;
}
```
